  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening COVID-19 Preparedness and Response in North-East Nigeria Through Targeted Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) Activities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM aims to support the reduction in vulnerabilities of crisis affected populations in north-east Nigeria against COVID-19 and contribute to the containment of the spread of the COVID-19 pandemic. To achieve this objective, IOM is strengthening COVID-19 preparedness and response efforts in the area of water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) in camps and camp-like settings, and surrounding host communities. Activities include hygiene promotion, sensitization and community engagement, provision of clean and safe water, distribution of essential hygiene and cleaning items, care and maintenance of sanitation facilities, installation of handwashing stations,  and management of the WASH core pipeline to ensure a steady stream of core relief supplies to partners for distribution to the affected population.</narrative>
  </description>
